<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17661022-41">
               <interp inst="t17661022-41" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17661022-41" type="year" value="1766"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17661022-41" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17661022"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17661022-41" type="date" value="17661022"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17661022-41-off208-c318" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-41-defend405 t17661022-41-off208 t17661022-41-verdict212"></join>
         
               <p>517. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17661022-41-defend405" type="defendantName">
                     Thomas 
                     Tool 
                  <interp inst="t17661022-41-defend405" type="surname" value="Tool"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-defend405" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-defend405" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17661022-41-off208" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-off208" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-off208" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing 19 yards of cloth, called bath coating, value 30 s. and three yards of blue duffil
            </rs>, the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17661022-41-victim407" type="victimName">
                     Mary 
                     Fullwood 
                  <interp inst="t17661022-41-victim407" type="surname" value="Fullwood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-victim407" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-victim407" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-41-off208 t17661022-41-victim407"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17661022-41-cd209" type="crimeDate">Aug. 15</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-41-off208 t17661022-41-cd209"></join>. ++</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17661022-41-person408">
                  Richard 
                  Wood 
               <interp inst="t17661022-41-person408" type="surname" value="Wood"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person408" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mrs. Fullwood, in <placeName id="t17661022-41-crimeloc210">Holywell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17661022-41-crimeloc210" type="placeName" value="Holywell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17661022-41-crimeloc210" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-41-off208 t17661022-41-crimeloc210"></join>, a <rs id="t17661022-41-viclabel211" type="occupation">woollen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17661022-41-victim407 t17661022-41-viclabel211"></join>. On the 15th of August we missed 19 yards of blue bath coating, and three yards of blue duffil; it was lying in the window when the clock struck eight in the evening; I turned about to put up the window shutter and it was gone; the other witnesses can give a farther account.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17661022-41-person409">
                  William 
                  Coney 
               <interp inst="t17661022-41-person409" type="surname" value="Coney"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person409" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person409" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker. On the 3d of September the prisoner brought a yard and quarter of blue bath coating to pledge; he said he bought it in Newgate-street; I recollected a bill I had from Sir 
               <persName id="t17661022-41-person410">
                  John 
                  Fielding 
               <interp inst="t17661022-41-person410" type="surname" value="Fielding"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person410" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , of such cloth stolen; I told him my suspicion; he then told me his mother gave it him; I sent for her; she was not at home; then I stopped it; (produced in court.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17661022-41-person411">
                  Sarah 
                  Ashby 
               <interp inst="t17661022-41-person411" type="surname" value="Ashby"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person411" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person411" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner's mother brought this cloth to me about three months ago; (producing a piece of blue cloth)</p>
               <p>Q. to Wood. Look at those pieces; are you able to swear to them?</p>
               <p>Wood. There not being marks on them, I am not; they are like the cloth I lost; I believe it is part of it, but do not swear it is; the prisoner gave different accounts how he came by it; first of all he said he had had it 5 years, then 5 months,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176610220029"></xptr> then 5 weeks, then 5 days, then he had it no longer than from Saturday till Monday.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>This cloth I had of my mother; I was a little short of money and I went to pawn it, and they stopped it.</p>
               <p>To his character.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17661022-41-person412">
                  John 
                  Tool 
               <interp inst="t17661022-41-person412" type="surname" value="Tool"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person412" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-person412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was bred a bricklayer by trade; I never knew him bear any other character than an honest, civil, working, good-natured lad.</p>
               <p>Q. Are you any way related to him?</p>
               <p>Tool. If I do not mistake he is my son.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17661022-41-verdict212" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17661022-41-verdict212" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               Acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
